bits.description: New rising edge detected

fields.name: wnR
fields.description: Week number of last rising edge

fields.name: wnF
fields.description: Week number of last falling edge

fields.name: towSubMsR
fields.description: Millisecond fraction of tow of rising edge in nanoseconds

fields.name: towSubMsF
fields.description: Millisecond fraction of tow of falling edge in nanoseconds

fields.name: towMS
fields.description: Time pulse time of week according to time base

fields.name: week
fields.description: Time pulse week number according to time base

bits.name: timeBase
bits.description: Time base: 0 = Time base is GNSS, 1 = Time base is UTC

bits.name: utc
bits.description: UTC: 0 = UTC not available, 1 = UTC available

bits.name: raim
bits.description: (T)RAIM information: 0 = Information not available, 1 = Not active, 2 = Active

bits.name: qErrInvalid
bits.description: qErr validity: 0 = Quantization error valid, 1 = Quantization error invalid

bits.name: TpNotLocked
bits.description: TP lock status: 0 = Next TP is locked to GNSS, 1 = Next TP is based on local time and not locked to GNSS - week/tow may be invalid

bits.name: timeRefGnss
bits.description: GNSS reference information. Only valid if time base is GNSS (timeBase=0): 0 = GPS, 1 = GLONASS, 2 = BeiDou, 3 = Galileo, 4 = NavIC, 15 = Unknown

bits.name: utcStandard
bits.description: UTC standard identifier. Only valid if time base is UTC (timeBase=1): 0 = Information not available, 1 = Communications Research Laboratory (CRL) Tokyo Japan, 2 = National Institute of Standards and Technology (NIST), 3 = U.S. Naval Observatory (USNO), 4 = International Bureau of Weights and Measures (BIPM), 5 = European laboratories, 6 = Former Soviet Union (SU), 7 = National Time Service Center (NTSC) China, 8 = National Physics Laboratory India (NPLI), 15 = Unknown

fields.name: itow
fields.description: integer millisecond tow received by source

fields.name: deltaMs
fields.description: integer milliseconds of delta time (current time minus sourced time)
